<span id="fn_2503"></span>[155:2504](2070039.htm#fr_2503.md) <span
id="ii.xxvii-p55.1"></span>

<span id="ii.xxvii-p56"></span> Tertull. *De Bapt*. c. 20:  “For the
word had gone before ‘that no one untempted should attain to the
celestial kingdoms.’”  *Apost. Const*. II. viii.:  “The Scripture says,
‘A man that is a reprobate (<span class="Greek"><span
id="ii.xxvii-p56.1"></span>ἀ</span><span class="Greek"><span
id="ii.xxvii-p56.2"></span>δόκιμος</span>) is not tried (<span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xxvii-p56.3"></span>ἀ</span><span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xxvii-p56.4"></span>πείραστος</span>) by
God.’”  Resch, *Agrapha*, Logion 26, p. 188, quotes allusions to the
saying in [Jas. 1:12](../../../bib/kjv/jam001.htm#012.md),
[13](../../../bib/kjv/jam001.htm#013.md), [2 Cor.
13:5](../../../bib/kjv/co2013.htm#005.md),
[6](../../../bib/kjv/co2013.htm#006.md),
[7](../../../bib/kjv/co2013.htm#007.md)<span id="ii.xxvii-p56.5"></span>,
and concludes that it was recorded as a saying of our Lord in one of the
un-canonical gospels ([Luke i. 1](../../../bib/kjv/luk001.htm#001.md)<span
id="ii.xxvii-p56.6"></span>), where it occurred in the context of the
incident narrated in [Matt. 26:41](../../../bib/kjv/mat026.htm#041.md),
[Mark 14:38](../../../bib/kjv/mar014.htm#038.md)<span
id="ii.xxvii-p56.7"></span>.

<span id="fn_2504"></span>[155:2505](2070039.htm#fr_2504.md) <span
id="ii.xxvii-p56.8"></span>

<span id="ii.xxvii-p57"></span> [Jas. i.
2](../../../bib/kjv/jam001.htm#002.md)<span id="ii.xxvii-p57.1"></span>.

<span id="fn_2505"></span>[155:2506](2070039.htm#fr_2505.md) <span
id="ii.xxvii-p57.2"></span>

<span id="ii.xxvii-p58"></span> <span class="Greek"><span
id="ii.xxvii-p58.1"></span>ἀ</span><span class="Greek"><span
id="ii.xxvii-p58.2"></span>πεπνίγη</span>.  [Matt. xxvii.
5](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#005.md)<span id="ii.xxvii-p58.3"></span>: 
<span class="Greek"><span id="ii.xxvii-p58.4"></span>ἀ</span><span
class="Greek"><span id="ii.xxvii-p58.5"></span>πήγξατο</span>.

