<span id="ii.xxvii-p80"></span> In the Liturgy of St. James, after all
have communicated, “*The Deacons and the People say*:  Fill our mouths
with Thy praise, O Lord, and fill our lips with joy, that we may sing of
Thy glory, of Thy greatness, all the day.  *And again*:  We render
thanks to Thee, Christ our God, that Thou hast accounted us worthy to
partake of Thy Body and Blood, &c.”

